The paper deals with the problem of privately releasing data, which is a common concern in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The use of differential privacy is a key aspect of the paper, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The techniques presented in the paper involve summarizing and filtering data, which are common tasks in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the issue of sparse data, which is a topic of interest in the field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves the use of sampling and filtering methods, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT).
